description:
Early wake up for today as we ride south in order to catch our ferry to Shodoshima - an island in the Seto Inland Sea with a distinctly Mediterranean atmosphere. In one of our hilliest rides of the entire journey, we are forced up and down this island's rolling hills before arriving at Angel Road - a picturesque sandbar where we will have lunch.

After lunch we take another ferry back to the mainland, arriving at the Shin-Okayama port. From here we have our flattest ride through numerous rice fields and small villages, eventually making our way to Kurashiki - Japan's city of canals.
